So,

5
00:00:10.400 --> 00:00:11.070
it's always a good

6
00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:15.980
start. So we've been given a very grand title, Hematological

7
00:00:16.580 --> 00:00:19.460
Malignancies, Undruggable Targets and New Frontiers.

8
00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:21.180
And

9
00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:24.260
... Okay.

10
00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:29.380
There we go. And so, essentially what we were asked

11
00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:33.180
to do was to think about a little bit of some of the high-throughput

12
00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:37.040
technologies that have been developed, and how we

13
00:00:37.140 --> 00:00:41.080
can use these in heme malignancies to not only identify

14
00:00:41.100 --> 00:00:44.380
targets, but also to help to guide our treatments.

15
00:00:44.940 --> 00:00:45.560
And so,

16
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:49.800
my name's Faith Davis. I'm a physician scientist based in

17
00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:50.580
NYU

18
00:00:51.380 --> 00:00:54.080
Langone, and I specialize in multiple myeloma.

19
00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.400
We are joined by my two esteemed

20
00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.280
colleagues. Dr. Pickman is the co-director

21
